"""Authorization fitness suite (T1–T4) — enforcement completeness is TESTED, not trusted.

T1 deny-by-default: every route is guarded, requires authentication, or is on an explicit public
allowlist. T1b: any route reaching a tenant DB (active_tenant in its dependency tree) MUST carry a
permission guard. T2: tenant routes bind their {tenant_id}. T3: no response model carries the authz
AST. T4: the permission/role vocabulary never appears on a client surface (OpenAPI or a 403 body).
"""

